HEADWORD: Electrolier
<hw>E*lec`tro*lier"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Formed from
<ets>electric</ets> in imitation of <ets>chandelier</ets>.]</ety> <def>A
branching frame, often of ornamental design, to support electric
illuminating lamps.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

